{"key":"post-10633980","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10633980</id>\n<content>Your face and wrists are two very sensitive parts of your body.&amp;nbsp; If your ambient humidity is 40% and you stick your face into a 99% humidity terrarium, it will feel moist.&amp;nbsp; However, if your ambient humidity is 8% and you stick your face into a 50% humidity terrarium, it will also feel moist, but certainly not enough for growing mushrooms.&amp;nbsp; That's why it isn't a valid hygrometer.&amp;nbsp; Pony up $30 and get a good one that can be calibrated via the damp towel method, OR build a shotgun terrarium per the tek and you'll just know it's OK.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10634527</next>\n<prev>10632427</prev>\n<first>10632386</first>\n<last>10634527</last>\n<when>1246953960</when>\n<utime>07/07/09 11:06 AM</utime>\n</post>"}